body.description: We’ve got your game with Approach® S12, a golf watch designed to turn on when you tee off. Get key yardages to the green, as well as to hazards and doglegs, on 42,000 preloaded courses worldwide. Keep score from the watch itself and upload directly to the Garmin Golf™ app (when paired with a compatible smartphone) to participate in weekly leaderboards. Pair with optional Approach® CT10 club tracking sensors (sold separately) for more automatic game tracking capabilities. Play longer with a battery life that holds up — get up to 15 hours in GPS mode.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Garmin Approach S12 Easy-to-Use GPS Golf Watch

KEEP SCORE Your watch keeps score so you can always know where you stand. Upload directly to the Garmin Golf app on your compatible smartphone to participate in weekly leaderboards. SUNLIGHT READABLE The new round watch design offers a high-resolution screen that’s easily readable on even the sunniest days. TAKE A SWING Pair with full set of Approach CT10 club tracking sensors for more tracking capabilities (sold separately).

42,000+ PRELOADED COURSES Your watch comes preloaded with more than 42,000 CourseView maps of golf courses around the world. When paired with the Garmin Golf app, wirelessly download updates for the course you play most often. GO GREEN Quickly reference the front, middle and back of the green so you have all the data you need for the perfect shot. BATTERY LIFE Internal, rechargeable battery provides up to 30 hours in GPS mode.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great watch at a good price!
reviews.reviewText: I really like this watch, does the basics really well and keeps some really handy stats too. Battery life is amazing - runs for six or seven rounds of golf.Best thing is it just gives you an accurate shot yardage eiyout breaking the bank.Recommend looking at this one for sure.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Golf GPS Watch, no BS.
reviews.reviewText: I'm 67 years old. I want a simple, reliable, accurate, look down and read the yards in big numbers, on a sunny day. I previously owned a S10 which did the same thing but the S12 does a bit more. I can add the CT10 sensors to the S12. I can pair it to my phone to look at stats afterwards. I can look at where the traps and water hazards are by a quick push of a button. It pairs quickly to the outerspace GPS machine floating around the earth. A black and white number screen, not color. I dont need color - I know what color the green is. I also like the price. I tried the S62 and didnt have the patience to remember what buttons to push to see info. All I need to know is how far the hole is and how far a hazard is. The S12 does it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 29, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Didn't know I needed a GPS watch until I got this
reviews.reviewText: I had been using a hand held range finder until one day I played with a group of men who all were wearing GPS watches. I looked it up, and purchased this. I also changed out the strap to a velcro loop style.Pros:Very light weight.Accuracy seems consistent with range finder, and it's much easier to get distance by looking at your wrist.Able to get lay-up distances, and distances to hazards.Relatively inexpensive.Good contrast in bright daylight, easy to read.Stroke entry works well.Cons:Fairway and hazard visualization is not as good as the expensive color models.Too many steps to "measure shot" or "change hole position"Battery life is as claimed, but it is too short and requires recharge too often.More steps than one would like to get distances to front and back of hazards.Other:Like any GPS watch, it doesn't actually know distance to the hole. My solution is, when in range of the green for the range finder, to compare the "Center of Green" from the watch to an actual range finder "distance to pin", and use the difference for other future shots at pin.To replace the original band, I recommend:https://smile.amazon.com/gp/product/B08DD57SHV/ref=ppx_yo_dt_b_search_asin_title?ie=UTF8&psc=1It is inexpensive, lightweight, and much easier to put on or remove.Overall, an excellent compromise between weight, cost, and functionality

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fits the Bill
reviews.reviewText: I bought this to replace a Garmin S60 that would not hold a charge. The battery cannot be replaced. Planned obsolescence, I am sure. Anyway, I never used all the features of the S60. All I want is a solid golf GPS watch, and this is it. I have played 2 rounds without recharging and the battery is still at about 75%. Much lighter and thinner than the S60. Very accurate when compared to friend’s GPS devices and range finder lasers. This is a winner. Incidentally, I bought a glass screen protector and rubber plugs for the charging port for a couple bucks. They came in a combo pack.I set the numbers to the larger format and they are super easy to see at a glance. The face is easy to read in bright sunlight. I really like this so far. I will update if needed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to use. Accurate
reviews.reviewText: Very accurate GPS Watch. Easy to use. Good battery life

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I scored big with this gift for my husband!
reviews.reviewText: I bought this is a Christmas gift for the husband who has everything. It was a hit! He used the watch almost immediately. My husband is at the golf course a couple of times a week. He says the watch is very easy to use and does everything he needs it to do. He says he loves that the watch keeps his score.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So good, never touch my hand-held laser again!
reviews.reviewText: The instructions are harder to read than using the product. Learn the button patterns in action on the first hole. First use it found my home course (New Mexico) after taking just a bit longer than expected to synch to the satellite. Put me on the correct hole - started on #10 on the back-side. Coolest part (I'll probably get over it, but) is watching the remaining yardage 'count down' as you walk to your next shot. Love that. Accuracy seems right on compared to on-course yardage markers (which my home course as precision few of). Yes, it is an entry-level yardage watch. For my talent level (9 hndp) it is perfect to inform my club selection. I would like the watch to be back-lit for around the clock wear. But, I quibble.
La verdad ni lo he sacado de su empaque, pero llego bien en forma y tiempo.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on July 29, 2021
reviews.reviewText: Easy to use and accurate definitely a good buy
No bells and whistles, just the basics, exactly what I was looking for. Very easy to use and courses load quickly. So far the battery life is quite good.

reviews.reviewTitle: This Garmin watch has a fantastic battery!
reviews.reviewText: My husband has been using the Garmin Approach S12 for four rounds on our 18 hole golf course where the average round takes about 4 hours. The battery is still at least 60% full! This Garmin watch is a simple version, but for someone that wants a long lasting battery and reliable distance control to the front, middle and back of a green, and is not interested in frills, this is the right watch!
Very pleased with length of charge held
